 identify the necessary team, establish roles, develop the plan, and carry the work through to publication and dissemination.')}</div></section>`,
'/people':()=>`${hero('People','RCC brings together researchers whose expertise fits the needs of specific projects. The Collaborative has continuing organizational leadership, while investigators, advisors, analysts, and institutional partners may participate in one or more projects.')}
<section class="section"><div class="shell">${heading('Leadership')}<article class="card person"><div class="portrait" aria-label="Michael Barros initials">MB</div><div><div class="eyebrow">Founding Director</div><h2>Michael Barros</h2><p>Michael Barros is the founding director of the Religious Cognition Collaborative and a PhD candidate in psychology whose research focuses on grounded cognition, dreams, religious experience, and the cognitive science of religion. His work combines quantitative analysis, theory development, and interdisciplinary scholarship. He directs the Collaborative’s research agenda, develops new projects, assembles project teams, and oversees research operations.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button dark" href="mailto:barrostheology@gmail.com">Contact</a></div></div></article></div></section>
<section class="section alt"><div class="shell">${heading('Current Project Team','The principal investigator and other project personnel will be listed after every name, role, affiliation, biography, photograph, and public listing has been verified and approved.')}<div class="empty-state">Project team information pending authorization.</div></div></section>`,
'/publications':()=>`${hero('Publications and Outputs','RCC shares research through peer-reviewed publications, books and chapters, preprints, conference presentations, datasets, methods, and public-facing research materials. Outputs are listed by project and attributed to the researchers who produced them.')}
<section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="empty-state"><h2>Institutional publications and project outputs are forthcoming.</h2><p>Selected work by RCC researchers may be included here when it is directly relevant to the Collaborative’s research program and its citation has been independently verified.</p></div></div></section>`,
'/collaborate':()=>`${hero('Collaborate With Us','RCC is built for research questions that benefit from expertise across disciplines, institutions, and traditions. We welcome serious inquiries from researchers, institutions, students, and technical specialists interested in developing or contributing to rigorous work on religion and cognition.')}
<section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="grid three">${card('For researchers','Researchers may approach RCC with a project concept, a dataset, a methodological need, or an interest in joining an existing project. Productive inquiries identify a clear question, the expertise already available, and the expertise or infrastructure still needed.')}${card('For institutions','RCC welcomes project-based relationships with universities, research centers, laboratories, nonprofit organizations, archives, and data repositories. Institutional collaborations should have a defined purpose, responsible contacts, and clear expectations regarding research oversight, funding, data, authorship, and public communication.')}${card('For students and early-career researchers','Opportunities may include research assistance, coding, literature review, data preparation, analysis, project coordination, and collaborative writing. Availability depends on active projects, supervision capacity, and the applicant’s skills and reliability.')}</div></div></section>
<section class="section alt"><div class="shell"><div class="grid two"><div class="prose"><h2>What to include in an inquiry</h2><ul><li>Your name, institution, and current role.</li><li>Your research interests and relevant expertise.</li><li>The project, question, dataset, or collaboration you are proposing.</li><li>The specific contribution you can make or support you are seeking.</li><li>Any relevant timeline, funding opportunity, or deadline.</li></ul></div>${form('Start a Conversation',['Name','Email','Institution or Organization','Current Role','Area of Expertise','Proposed Collaboration'],'Submit Inquiry')}</div></div></section>`,
'/support':()=>`${hero('Support Research','Independent research requires more than strong ideas. Participant compensation, data collection, software, analysis, research assistance, publication, and collaboration all require material support. Contributions help RCC develop and complete rigorous projects that might otherwise remain unfunded.')}
<section class="section"><div class="shell">${heading('Ways to Support the Work')}<div class="grid three">${card('General Research Fund','General support allows RCC to develop new projects, respond to emerging opportunities, and cover shared research costs that are not tied to a single restricted award.')}${card('Project Support','Donors and funders may support an approved project with a defined purpose, budget, leadership team, and anticipated outputs.')}${card('Institutional and Foundation Funding','RCC welcomes conversations with foundations, institutions, and philanthropic partners interested in supporting rigorous research on religion, cognition, consciousness, and human experience.')}</div></div></section>
<section class="section alt"><div class="shell"><div class="grid two"><div class="pro